erating social tension and facilitate public gathering in real life. User generated contents on social media can be explored to reveal insights to the researchers in discovering human emotions towards the real-world events. In spite of that, social tension detection research is still immature since limited number of reported literatures. Social tension detection is considered as emotion detection which is one of sentiment analysis task in Natural Language Processing (NLP) research area. Detecting social tension from social media textual data is a complicated task since emotions are not always explicitly expressed in text. This paper reviews the literature on previous works that have been conducted for social tension detection on social media textual data published after the year of 2010. ¬© 2020 EUROSIS-ETI.');
